            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;You can use asm comments (&lt;code&gt;asm(&quot;#start of something&quot;)&lt;/code&gt;), but emitting asm that doesn&apos;t even assemble is probably a GOOD idea in this case.  It makes sure you don&apos;t accidentally leave it in for an actual build and gimp the optimizer.    Also, I like your idea of using extended-asm syntax to put a unique ID on each clone of the statements is a good idea to help find multiple calls to a function.  I&apos;m not sure if &lt;code&gt;volatile&lt;/code&gt; stops the optimizer from cloning, though.  Maybe it can be cloned, as long as it still runs the right number of times.&lt;/span&gt;

